22:45.614 --> 22:47.150
...but I'm glad you did.

22:48.409 --> 22:50.695
It appears the reunion was a happy one?

22:50.870 --> 22:53.202
-Yes. Very much so.
-Enc,shush.

22:55.124 --> 22:56.660
Thank you.

22:57.877 --> 22:59.162
What's in the bag?

23:02.256 --> 23:04.963
I can't believe a witch
can make vampires do that.

23:05.175 --> 23:06.631
Well, I believe it.

23:06.802 --> 23:10.465
Of course, it would be safest if Eric
were to come with me...

23:10.639 --> 23:11.970
...but the choice is his.

23:12.141 --> 23:14.883
-|'m not leaving.
-I thought not.

23:17.146 --> 23:18.682
I leave you with this then.

23:22.151 --> 23:23.641
Are you kidding me?

23:23.819 --> 23:27.482
If we do not chain ourselves,
then we will all meet the sun together.

23:27.656 --> 23:31.990
I am going home where Jessica and I
will do the very same thing.

23:35.998 --> 23:38.489
If you care anything for him,
you will do this...

23:39.668 --> 23:42.159
...or it'll be his last day on Earth.

23:48.677 --> 23:50.213
[CAR HORN HONKS]

23:51.013 --> 23:53.004
MAN:
Get off the road.

23:54.308 --> 23:56.469
Motherfucker.

24:09.490 --> 24:11.776
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

24:14.620 --> 24:16.531
Ihearyou.

24:21.001 --> 24:22.457
Pam?

24:24.046 --> 24:27.834
Get your ass out here,
you prune-faced bitch.

24:29.385 --> 24:31.546
I ain't scared of you.

24:32.554 --> 24:35.546
You want me, come and get me.

24:35.724 --> 24:37.806
MARNE:
Hush,dean

24:37.977 --> 24:41.219
You'll wake even the dead.

24:41.689 --> 24:44.897
Oh, hell, no. You're the second
to the last person I wanna see.

24:45.067 --> 24:48.651
Now, don't be too hard on Marnie.
Marnie's spirit is pure.

24:49.488 --> 24:53.902
And Tara ain't so crazy about Marnie's
new way of talking about herself.

24:54.076 --> 24:56.783
Marnie is no longer here.

24:57.913 --> 25:03.078
She's allowed me to reside within her
for the sacred work I've come to do.

25:04.420 --> 25:07.002
You may call me Antonia.

25:07.589 --> 25:09.545
Why should I call you anything?

25:09.717 --> 25:11.253
Because we are alike.

25:11.427 --> 25:14.885
Because we have both suffered
at the hands of vampires.

25:15.055 --> 25:20.015
They have raped us, fed on us.

25:20.185 --> 25:21.925
Am I right?

25:23.105 --> 25:24.436
How do you know that?

25:25.607 --> 25:27.438
It's written all over you.

25:27.943 --> 25:29.683
It's in your face.

25:30.446 --> 25:32.858
It's in your rage.

25:33.032 --> 25:34.442
It's in mine too.

25:36.118 --> 25:37.278
-Feel it.
-Let go of me.

25:37.453 --> 25:39.193
Feel it.

25:39.496 --> 25:41.202
[LAUGHS]

25:42.624 --> 25:44.125
[GROANS]

25:45.377 --> 25:51.088
Imagine our suffering multiplied,
spread over this entire earth.

25:51.258 --> 25:54.125
We are two among a sea of thousands,
millions...

25:54.303 --> 25:58.967
...who have been savaged by vampires
over the centuries.

25:59.141 --> 26:00.472
I know you want to fight.

26:01.769 --> 26:05.603
-I got no way of fighting back.
-I do.

26:05.773 --> 26:07.809
I can avenge our torment...

26:07.983 --> 26:14.320
...and the torment of every human
who has felt the stab of a vampire's fangs.

26:14.490 --> 26:17.903
But I cannot do it alone. I need you.

26:18.077 --> 26:22.241
Together, we can exact retribution.

26:24.833 --> 26:26.448
Okay.

26:28.504 --> 26:30.369
Say I help you.

26:33.175 --> 26:35.006
What do I have to do?

26:38.097 --> 26:41.589
VAMPIRE 1: Make sure it's all light tight.
VAMPIRE 2: Copy that.

26:42.392 --> 26:45.179
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

26:50.109 --> 26:52.065
[JESSICA SCREAMS]

26:53.195 --> 26:55.186
BILL:
Gently, please.

27:00.536 --> 27:03.118
I'm sorry we must do this.

27:05.040 --> 27:08.373
I used to have a whole box
of silver earrings and necklaces.

27:08.544 --> 27:11.707
My mom gave them to me when I was 13
since she never wore them...

27:11.880 --> 27:14.542
...but maybe one day I could.

27:15.467 --> 27:17.799
Oh, I hope Eden's got them now.

27:19.721 --> 27:21.632
Bucky. Give me the gloves.

27:22.558 --> 27:25.049
You stand down. I'll finish this.

27:33.527 --> 27:35.063
Okay.

27:37.739 --> 27:42.824
I mean, ain't gonna be nothing left for you
to save if you keep at it.

27:44.454 --> 27:47.742
-| feel like I'm dying.
-You will heal.

27:47.916 --> 27:49.531
I promise.

28:03.432 --> 28:04.592
That's good enough.

28:10.439 --> 28:12.430
Twice that on me.

28:15.944 --> 28:19.061
Okay. Last one.

28:31.293 --> 28:33.955
[GROANING]

28:50.270 --> 28:52.101
[SCREAMING]

28:53.273 --> 28:55.309
Fuck me.

29:01.114 --> 29:03.196
[ERIC GROANS]

29:05.285 --> 29:07.492
ERIC:
It must be pretty strong.

29:09.998 --> 29:12.660
You're the strongest vampire I know.

29:15.087 --> 29:20.002
It's like I've been drained.

29:20.175 --> 29:21.631
I know.

29:24.846 --> 29:26.757
I'm sorry.

29:27.391 --> 29:32.181
-Uh.... Fuck.
-|'ve lost too many people in my life.

29:32.354 --> 29:34.686
I can't lose you too.

29:35.357 --> 29:36.847
I understand.

29:37.025 --> 29:38.561
Okay.

29:49.329 --> 29:51.320
It'll be dawn soon.

29:51.707 --> 29:56.076
I hope-- No, I'm sure this is enough.

29:58.714 --> 30:00.705
Will you stay with me?

30:19.151 --> 30:21.312
I remember another one,
a girl in Agua Nueva.

30:21.486 --> 30:26.355
She was.... She was in labor
and losing a lot of blood.

30:26.533 --> 30:29.400
The doctors wanted to cut the baby
out of her...

30:29.578 --> 30:31.409
...but that might kill the mother too.

30:31.580 --> 30:35.414
The abuela called for Tio Luca,
and my tio, he came...

30:35.625 --> 30:37.911
...and he put his hand on her belly...

30:38.503 --> 30:41.336
...said a prayer to Santa Margarita.

30:42.924 --> 30:45.256
And they both lived.

30:46.094 --> 30:50.087
Tio Luca said that every life he saved
cost him a little bit of his own.

30:51.099 --> 30:53.181
I thought he was gone...

30:53.352 --> 30:56.264
...but he came back for his Jesusito.

30:59.274 --> 31:01.606
Old Luca could have warned me.

31:01.777 --> 31:05.611
I felt like a giant ass puppet
for your ghost uncle.

31:05.781 --> 31:07.692
Don't you see how rare this is?

31:07.866 --> 31:11.609
You and Marnie are the only people
that I've ever met...

31:11.787 --> 31:14.244
...who can connect with the dead.

31:15.290 --> 31:18.453
Being a medium is a serious calling.

31:18.627 --> 31:22.620
-| wish I didn't always have to answer.
-You don't have a choice.

31:23.298 --> 31:24.629
You are the answer.

31:27.094 --> 31:28.959
Oh, hell.

31:31.306 --> 31:33.262
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

31:33.683 --> 31:36.811
-Hello.
-Hey, beautiful. It's Sam.

31:36.978 --> 31:38.718
What's going on?

31:39.481 --> 31:40.891
Hold on a second.

31:48.990 --> 31:51.732
-Are you serious?
-Dead serious.

31:51.910 --> 31:54.822
In fact,
beautiful may be an understatement.

31:56.498 --> 32:01.834
Okay. How can I say this
in a way you won't misinterpret?

32:02.003 --> 32:03.914
Fuck you.

32:05.966 --> 32:07.331
Well--

32:11.430 --> 32:13.637
-Are they in?
-Yeah.

32:13.807 --> 32:14.842
Plus a few others.

32:16.435 --> 32:20.724
The bigger we can make the circle,
the better we can protect ourselves.

32:22.190 --> 32:24.522
Tara, honey, I got no home.

32:24.693 --> 32:27.935
Okay, three pieces of furniture
and two sons.

32:28.113 --> 32:32.197
They're gonna live with their daddy
if I don't get back on my feet.

32:34.953 --> 32:38.537
-I shouldn't be getting involved.
-We can fight back.

32:38.748 --> 32:42.161
Marnie's getting strong, really strong.

32:42.335 --> 32:44.371
And she needs us.

32:47.340 --> 32:48.955
Now, I can run away and hide...

32:49.134 --> 32:52.217
...or I can hold my ground
and stand up for myself.

32:53.847 --> 32:56.213
You remember who told me that?

32:59.561 --> 33:01.722
Shoot

33:03.064 --> 33:07.398
Well, if we're gonna go down,
might as well go down swinging.

33:07.903 --> 33:09.564
Yes.

33:09.738 --> 33:14.027
-But we're not going down.
-We better not.

33:15.911 --> 33:17.902
BEVERLEEN: You on board?
-In the boat.

33:18.079 --> 33:20.912
-Ha, ha. I knew it.
-I wasn't gonna do it without you.

33:21.082 --> 33:24.245
We can't stop now.
We each need to bring in at least one more.

33:24.419 --> 33:28.753
Well, I can ask my boyfriend. He's got great
spiritual energy when he's not stoned.

33:28.924 --> 33:32.667
My ex-sister—in-Iaw's in town.
She never liked vampires.

33:33.261 --> 33:35.422
I don't know any other people.

33:35.597 --> 33:38.839
The more the better.
If we can make the circle strong enough...

33:39.017 --> 33:42.009
...we'll be safe from vampires for good.

33:42.604 --> 33:44.435
[INDISTINCT CHATTER
OVER RADIO]

33:49.277 --> 33:51.563
What's it gonna feel like?

33:52.447 --> 33:54.108
Do you know?

33:54.616 --> 33:57.449
We won't be able to control our bodies.

33:57.619 --> 34:02.784
Whether our minds will be conscious,
I do not know.

34:02.958 --> 34:04.949
Oh, my God.

34:08.338 --> 34:09.874
I'm sorry.

34:11.132 --> 34:14.624
I've caused you so much suffering
in your human life...

34:15.470 --> 34:17.426
...and now in this one.

34:17.597 --> 34:19.212
No.

34:19.391 --> 34:21.632
I don't want you to ever be sorry.

34:21.810 --> 34:26.144
I've lived more with you than I ever
would have with my human parents.

34:28.233 --> 34:30.144
I never thanked you for that.

34:30.318 --> 34:32.058
We will survive this.

34:32.237 --> 34:35.821
Think of the life that you'll go back to.

34:37.117 --> 34:38.152
Think of Hoyt.

34:44.624 --> 34:47.957
I don't know ifl can go back to him.

34:50.380 --> 34:51.586
He loves me.

34:51.756 --> 34:56.841
Bill, he loves me so much
it hurts to even think about it.

34:59.848 --> 35:02.134
But I don't love him the same.

35:04.185 --> 35:06.267
I think if I was still human, I would.

35:06.438 --> 35:08.019
I know that I would...

35:08.898 --> 35:12.857
...but I don't have a human heart
anymore.

35:13.028 --> 35:14.359
Yes, you do.

35:14.529 --> 35:16.440
If you've fallen out of love with him...

35:16.615 --> 35:19.903
...it doesn't mean
that you've lost your humanity.

35:21.953 --> 35:26.196
We are, at our core, human.

35:26.416 --> 35:29.203
It's a human's fault
we're burning like bacon.

35:29.377 --> 35:33.541
And she was driven to it
by the acts of vampires.

35:33.715 --> 35:39.551
All these years
we indulged our murderous impulses...

35:39.721 --> 35:42.713
...Called it our nature.

35:43.224 --> 35:45.886
How could we not expect reprisal?

35:46.061 --> 35:48.643
Who cares who started it?

35:50.065 --> 35:52.556
She's hell bent on killing us.

35:53.902 --> 35:55.233
We have to kill her first.

36:01.242 --> 36:03.198
I've had...

36:04.746 --> 36:08.739
...175 years on this earth...

36:10.460 --> 36:13.577
...and I've accomplished so little good.

36:13.755 --> 36:15.837
If we survive...

36:16.007 --> 36:20.922
...when we survive the day...

36:24.099 --> 36:25.839
...I will put a stop to it.

36:26.017 --> 36:28.349
But you have done good.

36:30.563 --> 36:32.019
You made me.

36:33.108 --> 36:36.020
And when we survive the day...

36:36.736 --> 36:40.854
...I am going to eat that fucking witch...

36:41.866 --> 36:44.118
...starting with her face.

36:47.414 --> 36:51.407
ERIC: What time is it?
-It must be past noon by now.

36:53.878 --> 36:55.994
The spell hasn't come.

36:58.633 --> 37:00.373
It may not come at all.

37:00.552 --> 37:01.917
Maybe not.

37:02.095 --> 37:03.631
SooMe”.

37:05.473 --> 37:07.134
...remove the silver.

37:07.308 --> 37:09.640
I can't take that chance.

37:09.811 --> 37:12.427
There's still half a day of sunlight left.

37:12.605 --> 37:15.142
Ifl let you meet the sun...

37:15.734 --> 37:18.225
...I'd never forgive myself.

37:20.113 --> 37:23.526
King Bill said the witch is very powerful.

37:24.075 --> 37:25.986
So who knows?

37:27.454 --> 37:28.819
I may meet the sun anyway.

37:32.167 --> 37:35.034
I'd rather you didn't remember me
like this.

37:36.838 --> 37:40.171
There was one other time
I saw you under silver.

37:40.341 --> 37:44.004
You were in a Church full of people
who hated vampires.

37:44.179 --> 37:50.015
You said you'd give yourself up
in exchange for Godric and for me.

37:51.186 --> 37:54.178
Didn't sink in at the time...

37:54.355 --> 37:59.019
...but even then,
you were willing to die for me.

38:00.028 --> 38:02.360
And still you didn't love me.

38:02.530 --> 38:06.193
There was still that other stuff
that kind of blotted it out for me.

38:06.367 --> 38:08.653
I'd rather not think about it.

38:11.831 --> 38:13.696
Sookie, I don't want my memory back.

38:14.584 --> 38:16.449
Why not?

38:19.047 --> 38:21.880
If you can overlook the things I've done...

38:22.509 --> 38:24.875
...and forgive me for them...

38:26.387 --> 38:28.878
...I don't want to remember.

38:32.227 --> 38:35.719
I'm perfectly happy as I am with you.

38:37.315 --> 38:39.055
Me too.

38:42.237 --> 38:45.604
But I'm still not letting you out
of the silver.

38:52.747 --> 38:57.411
If we hadn't just laid off all our security
people, I'd have you thrown out.

38:57.585 --> 39:01.169
I'm not here to start a fight.
Why are you picking one with me?

39:02.131 --> 39:05.919
Is this that intimacy problem
you were talking about?

39:06.135 --> 39:10.424
Now, you know what my problem is?
I am a terrible judge of character.

39:10.598 --> 39:12.930
I let people into my life easily,
and I pay for it.

39:13.101 --> 39:16.935
-Thank you for reminding me.
-I thought we had a great time together.

39:17.772 --> 39:19.763
Have you been drinking?

39:19.941 --> 39:21.522
-Or drugs?
-No. Why would you--?

39:21.693 --> 39:24.435
Do you remember the last 24 hours
at all?

39:26.948 --> 39:28.529
Do you remember sleeping with me?

39:28.700 --> 39:31.942
I'm pretty sure I wouldn't forget that.

39:32.579 --> 39:34.740
Do you remember kicking me out
of your trailer?

39:34.914 --> 39:37.781
-What? No. When was that?
-Like 8:30.

39:38.459 --> 39:42.122
Yeah, I was over at the apartments.
There was no one in my trailer.

39:42.297 --> 39:45.630
-Unless my brother let himself in.
-He's not your twin brother, right?

39:45.800 --> 39:47.631
N0, he looks nothing-—

39:53.308 --> 39:55.549
Oh, fucking hell.

39:56.644 --> 39:59.135
Oh, fuck.

40:00.815 --> 40:04.307
Luna, that time you skinwalked
and got sick, tell me again what happened.

40:04.944 --> 40:06.650
-I ran a super high fever.
-Feven

40:06.821 --> 40:08.436
-And I threw up everything.
-Yeah.

40:08.615 --> 40:11.607
And I started vomiting blood.
Was your brother vomiting blood?

40:11.784 --> 40:13.649
Yeah, he was.

40:13.828 --> 40:15.443
Oh, my God.

40:15.997 --> 40:17.612
Oh, God.

40:19.000 --> 40:21.491
-Jesus Christ.
-Oh, I feel sick.

40:23.171 --> 40:25.662
Um, Hol, honey?

40:25.840 --> 40:30.675
Why is Andy Bellefleur asking for you
with a dozen Winn-Dixie roses in his hand?

40:30.845 --> 40:35.339
Oh, Christmas morning,
I completely forgot.

40:37.518 --> 40:39.975
-How do I look?
-Better than he deserves.

40:40.146 --> 40:43.479
-Have you been seeing Andy?
-So?

40:43.650 --> 40:44.685
What if I was?

40:44.859 --> 40:48.443
Well, me, Mikey and Terry are crammed up
in his bedroom for the time being...

40:48.613 --> 40:51.696
...so if you're fixing to get lucky,
might have to share the couch.

40:51.866 --> 40:54.608
-I wasn't even thinking about that.
-Between you and me.

40:54.786 --> 40:56.117
Their grandmama's a lush.

40:56.287 --> 40:58.198
And that house is falling apart, girl.

40:58.373 --> 41:02.616
Marrying into the Bellefleur family
ain't as glamorous as everyone says.

41:02.794 --> 41:05.035
Except for Terry. He's a prince.

41:05.254 --> 41:06.994
I ain't marrying anyone.

41:07.173 --> 41:09.710
We haven't even had one date yet.

41:09.884 --> 41:13.092
Hey, have Lafayette fry up his usual
for me.

41:13.262 --> 41:14.718
Mm-hm.

41:17.892 --> 41:20.053
Don't you be watching me.

41:23.064 --> 41:26.022
Well, aren't you handsome
all cleaned up?

41:27.235 --> 41:30.193
Thanks. Just bought the tie.

41:30.697 --> 41:34.235
-These are for you.
-Oh, you didn't have to.

41:34.409 --> 41:35.899
They were on sale.

41:37.495 --> 41:39.156
Should we grab a booth?

41:51.259 --> 41:52.920
So....

41:53.886 --> 41:57.925
-Where'd you end up staying the night?
-The La Crescenta Motel on Jefferson.

41:58.099 --> 42:00.090
Just till I find a rental.

42:00.309 --> 42:02.686
-That's nice.
-Oh, no. It's a dump.

42:03.104 --> 42:06.517
Right. Course it is.
I stayed there when I--

42:07.900 --> 42:09.891
I've stayed there.

42:10.570 --> 42:13.357
Whoo. That place.

42:13.531 --> 42:15.112
I'm sorry.

42:15.950 --> 42:17.941
You don't have to be nervous.

42:18.119 --> 42:21.077
You see me practically every day.

42:21.247 --> 42:22.828
It's just I haven't had any...

42:24.459 --> 42:25.744
...food today.

42:25.918 --> 42:28.785
I'm kind of off my game
when I haven't eaten.

42:28.963 --> 42:31.750
Well, the chef is already at work
on your favorite.

42:31.924 --> 42:32.959
I saw to that.

42:33.134 --> 42:37.218
I should be the making you feel better,
what with the....

42:37.388 --> 42:38.468
[IMITATES EXPLOSION NOISE]

42:38.639 --> 42:39.765
I feel fine.

42:39.932 --> 42:41.468
You don't have to worry about me.

42:44.645 --> 42:46.727
Are you okay?

42:48.566 --> 42:51.558
[GROANS]

42:55.782 --> 42:58.319
I'm just not feeling so--

42:58.826 --> 43:00.487
Like, I don't know why I'm--

43:01.496 --> 43:03.157
You know what?

43:03.998 --> 43:06.159
This was a bad idea.

43:06.334 --> 43:07.915
Sorry.

43:23.017 --> 43:25.178
Hey, you little booger.

43:26.020 --> 43:27.760
Peek-a-boo.

43:33.194 --> 43:36.402
What the--
Get out of my kitchen.

43:40.451 --> 43:42.362
Shh.

43:42.537 --> 43:44.243
[SPEAKS IN FRENCH]

43:44.539 --> 43:47.702
-Maman will pass for you.
-Lady, quit it. You hear me?

43:48.251 --> 43:51.664
[SINGING IN FRENCH]

44:06.727 --> 44:09.890
-Hey!
-Good Lord, Lafayette.

44:10.064 --> 44:12.555
You scared the stuffing out of me.

44:15.153 --> 44:18.065
[MOANING]

44:20.741 --> 44:22.242
You okay?

44:22.410 --> 44:23.900
Want to slow down?

44:24.579 --> 44:25.659
No.

44:27.373 --> 44:28.909
Keep going.

44:29.250 --> 44:30.740
No, wait.

44:30.918 --> 44:32.579
Scoot off.

44:48.102 --> 44:49.763
Baby, hold on.

44:51.689 --> 44:53.270
What's the matter?

44:54.942 --> 44:56.603
I'm sorry.

44:57.612 --> 44:59.102
I'm trying.

45:00.281 --> 45:01.771
Why you even gotta try?

45:08.956 --> 45:10.457
Iguessun

45:13.961 --> 45:18.455
I keep thinking about last night,
what we walked in on.

45:18.633 --> 45:20.043
What? Sookie and that vamp?

45:20.635 --> 45:23.752
-Are you in love with her?
-What?

45:23.930 --> 45:25.045
You kidding me?

45:25.223 --> 45:27.805
We're seriously having
this conversation? Now?

45:27.975 --> 45:31.809
-You asked. I'm telling you.
-Baby, this is crazy.

45:31.979 --> 45:34.061
You're imagining things.

45:34.232 --> 45:36.814
Then why am I feeling this way?

45:37.109 --> 45:39.691
[SOBBING]

45:45.826 --> 45:48.317
All right, hey.

45:49.914 --> 45:51.324
Look at me.

45:51.499 --> 45:53.080
I worry for her.

45:53.251 --> 45:54.787
I do.

45:56.170 --> 45:58.331
That's as far as it goes.

46:00.341 --> 46:02.832
There's only one girl that I love.

46:04.178 --> 46:06.635
And only one girl that I dream about.

46:07.348 --> 46:10.135
I don't know why you're thinking
the things you are...

46:11.644 --> 46:17.184
...but all's I can say is that I'm here
and I'm yours.

46:21.487 --> 46:23.352
Forever?

46:23.656 --> 46:25.112
Yeah.

46:26.701 --> 46:28.362
Forever.

46:33.082 --> 46:35.539
[CHATTERING]

46:56.230 --> 46:58.061
Marnie?

46:59.400 --> 47:00.560
What's going on?

47:00.735 --> 47:03.067
My name...

47:03.904 --> 47:05.610
...is Antonia.

47:06.657 --> 47:12.573
I died at the hands of vampires
in the year 1610.

47:12.747 --> 47:16.239
Our brave and loyal friend Marnie...

47:16.417 --> 47:19.750
...has summoned me
from across the centuries...

47:19.920 --> 47:23.583
...for we are once again at war.

47:24.133 --> 47:27.921
But we are capable
of defending ourselves.

47:28.429 --> 47:30.420
I can Show you.

47:30.639 --> 47:34.928
If you do not wish to join me, go now.

47:35.102 --> 47:39.436
I seek only the assistance of the willing.

47:44.278 --> 47:46.360
Hey, where you going?

47:48.115 --> 47:49.525
Cowards.

47:49.700 --> 47:54.444
Let them go if they cannot stand with us.

47:54.663 --> 47:58.702
This group had a traitor once.

47:58.876 --> 48:02.960
She betrayed our names to the vampires.

48:03.130 --> 48:05.746
She has paid for it.

48:08.803 --> 48:11.465
We are no longer hidden.

48:11.639 --> 48:15.302
If we do nothing and wait,
we shall be tortured...

48:20.398 --> 48:22.810
But understand this.

48:23.734 --> 48:28.444
Vampires are not immortal.

48:30.658 --> 48:33.445
They're only harder to kill.

48:34.495 --> 48:38.784
And that is where our humanity
is our great advantage...

48:38.958 --> 48:44.669
...for our human spirits are immortal.

48:45.172 --> 48:50.337
I stand before you as living proof
of this very fact.

48:50.511 --> 48:56.848
I have matched my human spirit
against their emptiness...

48:57.017 --> 49:00.180
...and I have won.

49:00.354 --> 49:04.768
Now I require your support,
so we may do so again.

49:04.942 --> 49:11.233
Let us show these vampires
the fury and power of the human spirit.

49:12.324 --> 49:16.658
We have waited 400 years for this.

49:18.122 --> 49:21.535
